vidence Oatlhotse]], [[Onkemetse Linda Francis]] and [[Refilwe Tsutsu Gabatshwana]].\n\n== Cycling ==\n{{Main|Cycling at the 2019 African Games}}\n\nBotswana competed in events in both road cycling and mountain bike cycling.<ref name=\"montsho_going_strong\"/>\n\n== Judo ==\n{{Main|Judo at the 2019 African Games}}\n\n[[Thato Lebang]], [[Tirelo Lekoko]], [[Edwin Sello]], [[Letlhogile Tsheko]], [[Gwafila Tema]], [[Happy Taukobong]], [[Victoria Leagajang]] and [[Lucky Mabaka]] will represent Botswana in judo.<ref name=\"montsho_going_strong\"/>\n\n== Karate ==\n{{Main|Karate at the 2019 African Games}}\n\nBotswana competed in karate.<ref name=\"montsho_going_strong\"/> In total athletes representing Botswana won four bronze medals.\n\n== Swimming ==\n{{Main|Swimming at the 2019 African Games}}\n\nSix athletes represented Botswana in swimming.<ref name=\"montsho_going_strong\"/>\n\n;Men\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!colspan=\"2\"|Heat\n!colspan=\"2\"|Final\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Time\n!Rank\n!Time\n!Rank\n|-\n|align=left rowspan=3|[[Solomon Dzingai]]\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Men's 50 metre freestyle|50 m freestyle]]\n|26.40\n|33\n|colspan=2|Did not advance\n|-\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Men's 100 metre freestyle|100 m freestyle]]\n|57.56\n|27\n|colspan=2|Did not advance\n|-\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Men's 200 metre freestyle|200 m freestyle]]\n|2:19.05\n|16\n|colspan=2|Did not advance\n|-\n|align=left rowspan=5|[[Ethan Fischer]]\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Men's 50 metre breaststroke|50 m breaststroke]]\n|31.71\n|21\n|colspan=2|Did not advance\n|-\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Men's 100 metre breaststroke|100 m breaststroke]]\n|1:08.72\n|15\n|colspan=2|Did not advance\n|-\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Me