ze:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!colspan=\"2\"|Heat\n!colspan=\"2\"|Final\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Time\n!Rank\n!Time\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Kitso Matija]]<br>[[Naomi Ruele]]<br>[[Caitlin Loo]]<br>[[Adrian Robinson (swimmer)|Adrian Robinson]]\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 4 \u00d7 100 metre mixed freestyle relay|4\u00d7100 m freestyle relay]]\n|3:58.76\n|9 '''QR'''\n|3:57.66\n|8\n|-\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Naomi Ruele]]<br>[[Adrian Robinson (swimmer)|Adrian Robinson]]<br>[[Caitlin Loo]]<br>[[Kitso Matija]]\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 4 \u00d7 100 metre mixed medley relay|4\u00d7100 m medley relay]]\n|4:15.65\n|5 '''Q'''\n|4:16.45\n|7\n|}\n\n== Taekwondo ==\n{{Main|Taekwondo at the 2019 African Games}}\n\nBotswana competed in Taekwondo.<ref name=\"montsho_going_strong\"/> Two athletes represented Botswana: [[Karabo Kula]] and [[Wardell Ernest Samothsozo]]. Kula won the bronze medal in the women's \u201346 kg event.<ref name=\"taekwondo_kula_profile\">{{cite web|url=https://www.jar2019.ma/resultats/eng/zb/engzb_taekwondo-athlete-profile-n1019287-kula-karabo.htm|title=Karabo Kula - Athlete Profile|website=2019 African Games|accessdate=30 September 2019|archive-date=30 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190930112207/https://www.jar2019.ma/resultats/eng/zb/engzb_taekwondo-athlete-profile-n1019287-kula-karabo.htm|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Tennis ==\n{{Main|Tennis at the 2019 African Games}}\n\n[[Denzel Seetso]], [[Mark Nawa]], [[Tshegofatso Tsiang]] and [[Ekua Refilwe Youri]] will represent Botswana in tennis.<ref name=\"montsho_going_strong\"/>\n\n== Volleyball ==\n{{Main|Volleyball at the 2019 African Games}}\n\nIn June 2019 [[Botswana women's national volleyball team]] competed in the [[Volleyball at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Women's tournament|women's tournament]] at the 2019 African Games.<ref name=\"volleyball_women_qualified\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cavb.org/2019/06/07/mozambique-men-botswana-women-through-to-aag-finals/|title=Mozambique Men, Botswana women through to AAG finals|date=7 June 2019|publisher=Conf\u00e9d\u00e9ration Africaine de Volleyball|accessdate=28 July 2019|archive-date=28 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728120651/https://www.cavb.org/2019/06/07/mozambique-men-botswana-women-through-to-aag-finals/|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Botswana men's national volleyball team|men's team]] was also scheduled to compete but ultimately did not compete.<ref name=\"kenya_volleyball_women_ready\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2019-08/07/c_138291232.htm|title=Kenya women's volleyball team ready to defend African Games title|date=7 August 2019|publisher=xinhuanet|accessdate=10 August 2019|archive-date=10 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810121824/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2019-08/07/c_138291232.htm|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Weightlifting ==\n{{Main|Weightlifting at the 2019 African Games}}\n\nBotswana is scheduled to compete in weightlifting.<ref name=\"montsho_going_strong\"/> Four athletes are scheduled to compete: [[Bokang Alphius Kagiso]], [[Kgotla Alphius Kgaswane]], [[Magdeline Moyengwa]] and [[Dikabelo Solomon]].\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Botswana at the African Games]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Nations at the 2019 African Games}}\n\n[[Category:Nations at the 2019 African Games]]\n[[Category:Botswana at the African Games|2019]]\n[[Category:2019 in Botswana sport|African Games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox country at games\n| NOC               =  BOT\n| NPC               = \n| IAAF              = \n| CGA               = \n| NF                = \n| country           = Botswana\n| year              = 2019\n| games             = African Games\n| games_link        = 2019 African Games\n| flag              = \n| flagcaption       = [[Flag of Botswana]]\n| alt               = \n| oldcode           = \n| NOCname           = [[Botswana National Olympic Committee]]\n| NPCname           = \n| CGAname           = \n| NFname            = \n| fedname           = \n| website           = \n| location          = Rabat, Morocco\n| start_date        = {{Start date|2019|08|19|df=y}}\n| end_date          = {{End date|2019|08|31|df=y}}\n| date              = \n| competitors       = 103\n| competitors_men   = 60\n| competitors_women = 43\n| sports            = 12\n| events            = \n| flagbearer        = \n| flagbearer_open   = \n| flagbearer_close  = \n| rank              = 13\n| gold              = 5\n| silver            = 3\n| bronze            = 6\n| officials         = \n| appearances       = \n| app_begin_year    = \n| app_interval      = \n| summerappearances = \n| winterappearances = \n| youthappearances  = \n| seealso           = \n| previous          = \n| next              = \n}}\n'''[[Botswana]]''' competed at the '''[[2019 African Games]]''' held from 19 to 31 August 2019 in [[Rabat]], Morocco.<ref name=\"oc_ultimate_guide\">{{cite web|url=https://www.olympicchannel.com/en/stories/features/detail/rabat-2019-morocco-african-games-preview/|title=Things you need to know about the Rabat 2019 African Games|date=27 July 2019|publisher=Olympic Channel|accessdate=27 July 2019|archive-date=27 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727185045/https://www.olympicchannel.com/en/stories/features/detail/rabat-2019-morocco-african-games-preview/|url-status=live}}</ref> In total 103 athletes represented Botswana at the games.<ref name=\"botswana_gov_to_fund\">{{cite web|url=https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1083304/botswana-govt-funds-african-games-preps|title=Botswana Government fund country's team to compete in African Games|date=10 August 2019|publisher=Inside the games|accessdate=10 August 2019|archive-date=10 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810171356/https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1083304/botswana-govt-funds-african-games-preps|url-status=live}}</ref> Athletes representing Botswana won five gold medals, three silver medals and six bronze medals and the country finished in 13th place in the medal table.\n\n== Medal summary ==\n\n=== Medal table ===\n\n{{col begin}}\n| \u00a0style=\"text-align:left; width:78%; vertical-align:top;\"|\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%\"\n|-\n! Medal\n! Name\n! Sport\n! Event\n! Date\n|-\n| {{gold medal}} || {{sortname|Leungo|Scotch}} || [[Athletics at the 2019 African Games|Athletics]] || [[Athletics at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Men's 400 metres|Men's 400 metres]] || {{dts|28 August}}\n|-\n| {{gold medal}} || {{sortname|Galefele|Moroko}} || [[Athletics at the 2019 African Games|Athletics]] || [[Athletics at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Women's 400 metres|Women's 400 metres]] || {{dts|28 August}}\n|-\n| {{gold medal}} || [[Zibani Ngozi]]<br>[[Ditiro Nzamani]]<br>[[Onkabetse Nkobolo]]<br>[[Leungo Scotch]] || [[Athletics at the 2019 African Games|Athletics]] || [[Athletics at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Men's 4 \u00d7 400 metres relay|Men's 4 \u00d7 400 metres relay]] || {{dts|29 August}}\n|-\n| {{gold medal}} || {{sortname|Mohamed|Otukile}} || [[Boxing at the 2019 African Games|Boxing]] || Men's flyweight (52 kg) || {{dts|29 August}}\n|-\n| {{gold medal}} || {{sortname|Keamogetse|Kenosi}} || [[Boxing at the 2019 African Games|Boxing]] || Women's featherweight (57 kg) || {{dts|29 August}}\n|-\n| {{silver medal}} || {{sortname|Naomi|Ruele}} || [[Swimming at the 2019 African Games|Swimming]] || [[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Women's 100 metre backstroke|Women's 100 metre backstroke]] || {{dts|24 August}}\n|-\n| {{silver medal}} || {{sortname|Aratwa|Kasemang}} || [[Boxing at the 2019 African Games|Boxing]] || Women's lightweight (60 kg) || {{dts|29 August}}\n|-\n| {{silver medal}} || [[Oarabile Babolayi]]<br/>[[Oratile Nowe]]<br/>[[Amantle Montsho]]<br/>[[Galefele Moroko]] || [[Athletics at the 2019 African Games|Athletics]] || [[Athletics at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Women's 4 \u00d7 400 metres relay|Women's 4 \u00d7 400 metres relay]] || {{dts|30 August}}\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}} || {{sortname|Karabo|Kula}} || [[Taekwondo at the 2019 African Games|Taekwondo]] || Women's -46 kg || {{dts|21 August}}\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}} || {{sortname|Naomi|Ruele}} || [[Swimming at the 2019 African Games|Swimming]] || [[Swimming at the 2019 African Games \u2013 Women's 50 metre backstroke|Women's 50 metres backstroke]] || {{dts|23 August}}\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}} || {{sortname|Ofentse|Bakwadi}} || [[Karate at the 2019 African Games|Karate]] || Men Kata individual || {{dts|26 August}}\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}} || Men's team || [[Karate at the 2019 African Games|Karate]] || Men Kata team || {{dts|26 August}}\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}} || Men's team || [[Karate at the 2019 African Games|Karate]] || Men Kumite team || {{dts|26 August}}\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}} || Women's team || [[Karate at the 2019 African Games|Karate]] || Women Kata team || {{dts|26 August}}\n|}\n| \u00a0style=\"text-align:left; width:22%; vertical-align:top;\"|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%; text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n!colspan=5|'''Medals by sport'''\n|-\n|'''Sport'''\n| style=\"background:#f7f6a8;\"| {{gold01}}\n| style=\"background:#dce5e5;\"| {{silver02}}\n| style=\"background:#ffdab9;\"| {{bronze03}}\n|'''Total'''\n|-\n|[[#Athletics|Athletics]]\n| style=\"background:#F7F6A8;\" |3\n| style=\"background:#DCE5E5;\" |1\n| style=\"background:#FFDAB9;\" |0\n|'''4'''\n|-\n|[[#Boxing|Boxing]]\n| style=\"background:#F7F6A8;\" |2\n| style=\"background:#DCE5E5;\" |1\n| style=\"background:#FFDAB9;\" |0\n|'''3'''\n|-\n|[[#Karate|Karate]]\n| style=\"background:#F7F6A8;\" |0\n| style=\"background:#DCE5E5;\" |0\n| style=\"background:#FFDAB9;\" |4\n|'''4'''\n|-\n|[[#Swimming|Swimming]]\n| style=\"background:#F7F6A8;\" |0\n| style=\"background:#DCE5E5;\" |1\n| s